%% TIMING OVERVIEW:
%% - Wave 3 Timing: T-1 week (Mock Cutover) and Go-Live Weekend
%% - Mock Cutover Duration: 2 days (full rehearsal)
%% - Final Cutover Duration: 8-12 hours (production)
%% 
%% DAY 1 SCHEDULE:
%% - Morning (4-6 hrs): Phase 1 - Financial Balances (GL Balances, GL Open Items)
%% - Afternoon (4-6 hrs): Phase 2 - Sub-Ledger Open Items (AP, AR)
%% - Evening (3-4 hrs): Phase 3 - Asset Balances (can overlap with Phase 2)
%% 
%% DAY 2 SCHEDULE:
%% - Morning (4-6 hrs): Phase 4 - Inventory Balances (Stock, Subcontractor, Physical Inv)
%% - Afternoon (3-4 hrs): Phase 5 - Open Procurement Documents (PO, PR)
%% - Afternoon (3-4 hrs): Phase 6 - Open Sales Documents (SO, Contracts) - Parallel with Phase 5
%% - Evening (2-3 hrs): Final Validation & Go-Live Preparation

%% PARALLEL PROCESSING OPPORTUNITIES:
%% 1. AP Open Items and AR Open Items can load in parallel (both depend on GL Balances)
%% 2. Asset Balances can overlap with Phase 2 (separate team members)
%% 3. Inventory types (Stock, Subcontractor, Physical Inv) can partially overlap
%% 4. Open PO and Open PR can run in parallel
%% 5. Open SO and Contracts can run in parallel
%% 6. Phase 5 (Procurement) and Phase 6 (Sales) can run in parallel

%% PREREQUISITES:
%% - Wave 1: 100% complete and validated (GL Accounts, Cost Centers, Profit Centers, Asset Master)
%% - Wave 2: 100% complete and validated (Vendors, Customers, Materials, Info Records, Pricing)
%% - Physical inventory count completed 48 hours before cutoff
%% - Data freeze in effect (no new transactions in ECC)
%% - All ECC closing activities complete through cutoff date
%% - ECC reconciliation reports generated and saved (Trial Balance, AP/AR Aging, Stock Value)

%% DATA CUTOFF RULES:
%% - Financial Data: Cutoff as of last day of month preceding Go-Live
%% - Inventory: Physical inventory count freeze 48 hours before cutover
%% - Open Documents: No new PO/SO creation during freeze period (24 hours)
%% - AP/AR: All invoices posted through final cutoff date
%% - Month-end closing activities must be complete before cutoff

%% MOCK CUTOVER VS FINAL CUTOVER:
%% Mock Cutover (T-2 weeks):
%% - Full Wave 3 execution in sandbox/QA system
%% - Data as of practice cutoff date (e.g., prior month-end)
%% - Complete validation and reconciliation
%% - Timing validation (can we complete in 2 days?)
%% - Issue identification and remediation planning
%% - Team training and readiness verification
%% 
%% Final Cutover (Go-Live Weekend):
%% - Production system (locked for migration)
%% - Final cutoff date (typically last day of month)
%% - All lessons learned from mock cutover applied
%% - Compressed timeline (8-12 hours vs. 2 days for mock)
%% - Real-time monitoring and issue resolution
%% - Go/No-Go decision at completion

%% SUCCESS CRITERIA (Go-Live Readiness):
%% MUST HAVE (Zero tolerance):
%% - GL Account Balances: Trial Balance matches ECC exactly (Debit = Credit, zero variance)
%% - AP Open Items: AP Aging matches ECC exactly (total and by aging bucket)
%% - AR Open Items: AR Aging matches ECC exactly (total and by aging bucket)
%% - Sub-ledger to GL reconciliation: AP sub-ledger = GL recon account, AR sub-ledger = GL recon account
%% 
%% CRITICAL (Minimal tolerance):
%% - Inventory Stock Balances: Stock value matches ECC (variance within $100 total)
%% - Fixed Asset Balances: Net Book Value matches ECC (variance within $100 total)
%% - Inventory value = GL Inventory Accounts
%% - Asset Net Book Value = GL Asset Accounts
%% 
%% IMPORTANT (Operational):
%% - Open PO count and value match ECC
%% - Open SO count and value match ECC
%% - Open PR count matches ECC
%% - Sales Contracts loaded and accurate
%% - All functional testing passed (posting, clearing, goods movement, delivery creation)
%% - No critical errors in migration logs
%% - All functional leads have signed off

%% BALANCE RECONCILIATION EMPHASIS:
%% Wave 3 is BALANCE-CRITICAL. The following reconciliations are MANDATORY with ZERO variance tolerance:
%% 1. Trial Balance reconciliation (Debit = Credit in both ECC and S/4HANA)
%% 2. AP Aging reconciliation (Total AP = ECC, all aging buckets match)
%% 3. AR Aging reconciliation (Total AR = ECC, all aging buckets match)
%% 4. Sub-ledger to GL reconciliation (AP sub-ledger = GL account 21000, AR sub-ledger = GL account 11000)
%% 5. Inventory value reconciliation (Stock value = GL inventory accounts 14000, 14100, 14200)
%% 6. Asset value reconciliation (Net Book Value = GL asset account, Accumulated Depr = GL accum depr account)
%% 
%% If ANY of these reconciliations fail, DO NOT proceed to Go-Live. Resolve all variances first.

%% OPEN ITEM ACCURACY:
%% - AP/AR open items must maintain aging accuracy (document dates, due dates, baseline dates)
%% - Assignment field (ZUONR) must be populated for future clearing
%% - Payment terms must be accurate for due date calculation
%% - Partial payments must be reflected correctly
%% - Special GL indicators (down payments, guarantees) must be retained
%% - Payment blocks and dunning blocks must be migrated correctly

%% LEGEND:
%% - Solid arrows (==>) = Sequential dependency (must wait for completion)
%% - Dotted arrows (-..->) = Parallel processing possible (can overlap)
%% - Thick red borders (5px) = Critical path - ZERO variance tolerance (Financial balances)
%% - Thick orange borders (5px) = Critical path - Minimal variance ($100) tolerance (Inventory)
%% - Thick borders (3-4px) = Important for operations or moderate complexity
%% - Thin borders (2px) = Standard complexity
%% - Colors:
%%   * Light Blue = Wave 1 & 2 Prerequisites
%%   * Red (FFCDD2) = Financial Balances - CRITICAL (GL, AP, AR)
%%   * Light Red (FFEBEE) = GL Open Items
%%   * Purple (E1BEE7) = Asset Balances
%%   * Orange (FFE0B2) = Inventory Balances - CRITICAL
%%   * Light Orange (FFF3E0) = Inventory Related (Subcontractor, Physical Inv)
%%   * Green (C8E6C9) = Open Procurement Documents (PO, PR)
%%   * Teal (B2DFDB) = Open Sales Documents (SO, Contracts)
%%   * Yellow (FFF9C4) = Final Validation (Warning - Critical checkpoint)
%%   * Green Success (4CAF50) = Go-Live

%% ROLLBACK PLAN:
%% If critical issues are identified during Wave 3 that cannot be resolved within the cutover window:
%% 1. STOP all migration activities immediately
%% 2. Do NOT open S/4HANA to users
%% 3. Activate ECC rollback (restore from backup if needed)
%% 4. Communicate No-Go decision to all stakeholders
%% 5. Schedule remediation activities
%% 6. Reschedule Go-Live after issues resolved
%% 
%% Rollback triggers:
%% - Trial Balance variance > zero
%% - AP or AR Aging variance > zero
%% - Critical system errors preventing posting
%% - Data corruption or integrity issues
%% - Major functional testing failures
%% - Inability to complete Wave 3 within cutover window

